description:
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CAMHS Practitioner CYP - IAPT Trainee, Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bexley Child &amp; Adolescent Mental Health Service (CAMHS)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 Year Fixed Term Contract commencing January 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 Hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to become part of the strategy to increase access to evidence-based interventions to children and young people with anxiety and/or depression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This intensive training post will equip the postholder to provide interventions based on CYP-IAPT principles which are consistent with the CBT training course. The post is a mixture of training based in London through NHS England/Kings College London (post graduate diploma) and direct therapeutic work based within Bexley CAMHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have suitable experience/qualifications and an interest in working with young people in mental health environment and would like to further develop your skills this could be the post for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bexley CAMHS is a friendly, busy and thriving CYP IAPT service, regarded as an accessible and effective service. Staff that work in Bexley CAMHS describe a warm and caring environment across the whole service. We are an equal opportunities employer. We would welcome applications from Black and Ethic Minority candidates to ensure our workforce is representative of the communities that we work with.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are based in a newly refurbished, purposely designed building at Park Crescent (Erith Hospital Site), Park Crescent, Erith DA8 3EE. The site is easily accessible from Kent, SE and East London, as well as parts of Essex and Surrey. There is parking on site and nearby streets. There are also excellent public transport links including a direct train to Erith from London Bridge in under 40 mins. Given current COVID-19 restrictions, there we are currently operating with a mix of home and clinic-based work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would join Bexley CAMHS at an exciting time of service development. We are initiating a whole service improvement to the patient journey, enabling children and families to access help earlier and enabling staff to have job plans better tailored to their expertise and development. We seek to appoint a CAMHS practitioner to work within the multidisciplinary team providing CBT treatment to children and families with anxiety and/or depression. You would work in a large friendly MDT in our Assessment and Treatment pathway alongside colleagues from a range of disciplines. The current service improvement means all staff will be able to have job plans which include clear expectations for numbers of clinical contacts, types of work (e.g. assessment, core intervention and ongoing specialist therapy) and caseload size.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On completion of training, we hope to have available a CAMHS practitioner/CBT therapist post within Bexley CAMHS at the next Banding to which you can apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxleas NHS Foundation Trust provides mental health, learning disabilities and community services to the London Boroughs of Bexley, Bromley and Greenwich. The Trust and CAMHS have recently been rated as Good by the CQC and has a culture of supporting staff, whilst providing excellent services within a robust clinical governance framework.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Dr Kate Doherty, Principal Clinical Psychologist or Dr Nidhi Dholakia-Wellens, Principal Clinical Psychologist on 020 3260 5200.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is a training position and so all candidates will need to apply for both the trainee role with our organisation and the KCL Post Graduate Diploma in Child and Young Person IAPT Therapy in order to be shortlisted (for more information about the course and minimum entry criteria, please see the brochures found on the annafreud.org &lt;/em&gt;website: &lt;em&gt;transforming-the-workforce- cyp-mh-workforce-development - recruit-to-train. Please complete your university application using the KCL University Application Guidance supplied.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 19th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants are required to undertake an Enhanced Disclosure via the Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxleas NHS Foundation Trust operates a Probationary Period, further details are available on request&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Kate Doherty, Principal Clinical Psychologist or Dr Nidhi Dholakia-Wellens, Principal Clinical Psychologist on 020 3260 5200&lt;/p&gt;
